{
  "texts": [
    "When the first generation of neuroscience databases were started, there were few standard practices for designing web-accessible databases.",
    "As documented by NIF, each database had a different mode of access, different data structure, and the use of standards was very limited.",
    "It was a time of tremendous technological fluidity, with standard features we take for granted today (e.g., RESTful web APIs) still being invented.",
    "The cloud did not exist, and attempts to build resources on the early version of a cloud-like system (\"the grid\") met with considerable challenges (Grethe et al., 2005).",
    "With today's emphasis on data sharing, increased attention is starting to be paid to these critical infrastructures and how they are constructed, operated, and evaluated (Nelson, 2022)."
  ]
}